dataIdInfo.idAbs: This map data layer represents the road centerlines for Rockland County, NY. The road centerline features are associated with an attribute table that contains information on street names. The road centerline data layer was originally based on tax map right of ways developed in 1987 and have been updated based on digital orthophotographs from 2000 thru 2013. Continual updates are made as needed. Spatial coordinate system is New York State Plane East, NAD83. Scale is 1:1200 (100' scale). Mapping accuracy meets National Map Accuracy Standards for 100' scale mapping.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: The Street centerline GIS layer was developed to be used for general mapping.

prcStep.stepDesc: Street centerlines were initially created in 1987 as part of the County-wide parcel file developed at a scale of 1:200 feet. To start, street centerlines were generated from tax map right-of-ways to create a preliminary street product. Attributes such as street name were then added based on the information contained within the tax maps. Since the creation of the initial street centerlines, the alignment of the streets has been and continues to be updated using orthophotography from 2000, 2004 and 2007. New streets and address updates are provided by The Rockland County E911 office as changes occur.
